{"data":{"allPostTitles":{"edges":[{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/accessibility/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/getting-started/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/mode-and-value/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/accessibility/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/format/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/getting-started/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/limits/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/orientation/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/ticks/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/tooltip/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/slider/types/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/how-to/customize-color-picker/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/how-to/disable-color-picker/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/how-to/hide-control-buttons/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/how-to/render-palette-alone/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}}]},"postBySlug":{"html":"<h1 id=\"overview\"><a href=\"#overview\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Overview</h1>\n<p>The <strong>ColorPicker</strong> is a user interface that lets user to pick a color either by selecting the color values or by adjusting the hue and opacity. It supports various color specifications like RGB (Red, Green, and Blue), HSV (Hue, Saturation, and Value), and Hex codes.</p>\n<h2 id=\"key-features\"><a href=\"#key-features\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Key Features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Inline Rendering</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Mode And Value</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Customization</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Accessibility</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Localization</strong></li>\n</ul>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"Overview The  ColorPicker  is a user interface that lets user to pick a color either by selecting the color values or by adjusting the hue…","fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/color-picker/","previous":{"html":"<h1 id=\"mode-and-value\"><a href=\"#mode-and-value\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Mode and Value</h1>\n<h2 id=\"rendering-palette-at-initial-load\"><a href=\"#rendering-palette-at-initial-load\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Rendering palette at initial load</h2>\n<p>By default, the <code class=\"language-text\">Picker</code> area will be rendered at initial load. To render the Palette area while opening the ColorPicker pop-up, specify the <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.Inputs.EjsColorPicker~Mode.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">mode</code></a> property as <code class=\"language-text\">Palette</code>.</p>\n<p>In the following sample, it will render the <code class=\"language-text\">Palette</code> at initial load.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"razor\"><pre class=\"language-razor\"><code class=\"language-razor\">&lt;div class=&quot;wrapper&quot;&gt;\n    &lt;h4&gt;Choose a color&lt;/h4&gt;\n    &lt;EjsColorPicker ID=&#39;element&#39; Mode=&quot;ColorPickerMode.Palette&quot;&gt;&lt;/EjsColorPicker&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;style&gt;\n.wrapper {\n    margin: 0 auto;\n    width: 300px;\n    text-align: center;\n}\n&lt;/style&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Output be like\n<img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/palette.png\" alt=\"color-picker\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"color-value\"><a href=\"#color-value\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Color value</h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.Inputs.EjsColorPicker~Value.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">value</code></a> property can be used to specify the color value to the ColorPicker. It supports either <code class=\"language-text\">three</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">six</code> digit hex codes. To include <code class=\"language-text\">opacity</code>, set the color value as <code class=\"language-text\">four</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">eight</code> digit hex code.</p>\n<p>In the following sample, the color value sets as <code class=\"language-text\">four</code> digit hex code, the last digit represents the <code class=\"language-text\">opacity</code> value.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"razor\"><pre class=\"language-razor\"><code class=\"language-razor\">&lt;div class=&quot;wrapper&quot;&gt;\n     &lt;h4&gt;Choose a color&lt;/h4&gt;\n     &lt;EjsColorPicker ID=&#39;element&#39;Value=&quot;035a&quot; ModeSwitcher=&quot;false&quot;&gt;&lt;/EjsColorPicker&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;style&gt;\n.wrapper {\n    margin: 0 auto;\n    width: 300px;\n    text-align: center;\n    }\n&lt;/style&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>Output be like\n<img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/color-value.png\" alt=\"color-picker\"></p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://help.syncfusion.com/cr/aspnetcore-blazor/Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor~Syncfusion.EJ2.Blazor.Inputs.EjsColorPicker~Value.html\"><code class=\"language-text\">value</code></a> property\nsupports hex code with or without <code class=\"language-text\">#</code> prefix.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>","id":"61abd35a-e727-5993-b62f-35b32ef70fc4","fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/mode-and-value/","parentPath":"color-picker","childPath":"mode-and-value","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4","header":"<div id=\"doc-right-toc\"><span>Contents</span>\n<ul>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h2\"><a href=\"#rendering-palette-at-initial-load\">Rendering palette at initial load</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h2\"><a href=\"#color-value\">Color value</a></li>\n</ul></div>","breadCrumb":"ColorPicker/Mode and Value","isReleaseNotes":false,"title":"Mode and Value in Blazor [Preview] ColorPicker component - Syncfusion","description":"Checkout and learn about Mode and Value in Blazor [Preview] ColorPicker component of Syncfusion Essential JS 2, and more details.","platform":"Blazor [Preview]","isRobots":true}},"next":{"html":"<!-- markdownlint-disable MD024 -->\n<h1 id=\"getting-started-with-essential-js-2-for-aspnet-core-razor-colorpicker-component-in-visual-studio-2019\"><a href=\"#getting-started-with-essential-js-2-for-aspnet-core-razor-colorpicker-component-in-visual-studio-2019\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Getting Started with Essential JS 2 for ASP.NET Core Razor ColorPicker Component in Visual Studio 2019</h1>\n<p>This article provides a step-by-step introduction to configure Essential JS 2 setup, build and publish a simple .NET Core Razor ColorPicker Component web application using the <a href=\"https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/vs/preview/\">Visual Studio 2019</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"prerequisites\"><a href=\"#prerequisites\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisites</h2>\n<p>The official prerequisites to create and run an ASP.NET Core Razor Components on Windows environment are described in the <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/client-side/spa/blazor/get-started?view=aspnetcore-3.0&#x26;tabs=visual-studio\">.NET Core Razor components documentation website</a>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/vs/preview/\">Visual Studio 2019 Preview</a> with the ASP.NET and web development workload</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet-core/3.0\">.NET Core SDK 3.0 Preview</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"create-a-razor-component-application-from-vs-2019\"><a href=\"#create-a-razor-component-application-from-vs-2019\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Create a Razor Component application from VS 2019</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Choose <strong>File > New > Project…</strong> in the Visual Studio menu bar.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/new-project.png\" alt=\"new project in aspnetcore razor\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Make sure <strong>.NET Core</strong> and <strong>ASP.NET Core 3.0</strong> are selected at the top.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/razor-components-template.png\" alt=\"select framework\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Choose the <strong>Razor Components</strong> template and change the application name, and then click <strong>OK</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"importing-essential-js-2-razor-components-in-the-application\"><a href=\"#importing-essential-js-2-razor-components-in-the-application\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Importing Essential JS 2 Razor components in the application</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Now, add the <strong>Syncfusion.EJ2.AspNet.Core.RazorComponents</strong> NuGet package to the new application by using the NuGet Package Manager. Right-click the project and select Manage NuGet Packages.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/nuget-explorer.png\" alt=\"nuget explorer\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Search the <strong>Syncfusion.EJ2.AspNet.Core.RazorComponents</strong> keyword in the Browse tab and install <strong>Syncfusion.EJ2.AspNet.Core.RazorComponents</strong> NuGet package in the application.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/select-nuget.png\" alt=\"select nuget\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The Essential JS 2 package will be included in the project, after the installation process is completed.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Open <strong>~/_ViewImports.cshtml</strong> file and import the <code class=\"language-text\">Syncfusion.EJ2.RazorComponents</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\">@addTagHelper *, Syncfusion.EJ2.RazorComponents</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add the client-side resources through CDN or local npm package in the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;head&gt;</code> element of the <strong>~/wwwroot/index.html</strong> page.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/import-cdn.png\" alt=\"import cdn\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Now, add the Syncfusion Essential JS 2 ColorPicker component in any web page (cshtml) in the <code class=\"language-text\">Pages</code> folder. For example, the ColorPicker component is added in the <strong>~/Pages/Index.cshtml</strong> page.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;EjsColorPicker ID=&quot;element&quot;&gt;&lt;/EjsColorPicker&gt;</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Run the application. The Essential JS 2 ColorPicker component will render in the web browser.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/production/blazor/documentation/color-picker/images/color-picker.png\" alt=\"ColorPicker Sample\"></p>\n</li>\n</ol>","id":"a30ab617-381b-51d1-a540-2db50a859d97","fields":{"slug":"/color-picker/getting-started/","parentPath":"color-picker","childPath":"getting-started","gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4","header":"<div id=\"doc-right-toc\"><span>Contents</span>\n<ul>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h2\"><a href=\"#prerequisites\">Prerequisites</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h2\"><a href=\"#create-a-razor-component-application-from-vs-2019\">Create a Razor Component application from VS 2019</a></li>\n  <li class=\"doc-anchor-h2\"><a href=\"#importing-essential-js-2-razor-components-in-the-application\">Importing Essential JS 2 Razor components in the application</a></li>\n</ul></div>","breadCrumb":"ColorPicker/Getting Started","isReleaseNotes":false,"title":"Getting started with Blazor [Preview] ColorPicker component - Syncfusion","description":"Checkout and learn about getting started with Blazor [Preview]  component of Syncfusion Essential JS 2, and more details.","platform":"Blazor [Preview]","isRobots":true}},"gcse":"014729256687841406486:qzbiyd0sri4","header":"","breadCrumb":"ColorPicker/","isReleaseNotes":false,"title":"Blazor [Preview] ColorPicker component - Syncfusion","description":"Checkout and learn about getting started with Blazor [Preview] ColorPicker component of Syncfusion Essential JS 2, and more details.","platform":"Blazor [Preview]","isRobots":true}}